misconceptions.remediation_hint:
Rewrite the inner loop so that it controls and increments `j`, not `row`. For example:

`for (int row = 1; row <= N; row++) {
    for (int j = 1; j <= row; j++) {
        System.out.print("*");
    }
    System.out.println();
}`

Practice tracing small nested-loop examples on paper, updating each loop variable step by step, to see how many times each loop executes and why.

